.TH "gen_replace_estimator" 9 "gen_replace_estimator" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_replace_estimator \- replace rate estimator configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gen_replace_estimator
.BI "(struct gnet_stats_basic_packed *bstats "  ","
.BI "struct gnet_stats_basic_cpu __percpu *cpu_bstats "  ","
.BI "struct net_rate_estimator __rcu **rate_est "  ","
.BI "spinlock_t *lock "  ","
.BI "seqcount_t *running "  ","
.BI "struct nlattr *opt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bstats" 12
basic statistics
.IP "cpu_bstats" 12
bstats per cpu
.IP "rate_est" 12
rate estimator statistics
.IP "lock" 12
lock for statistics and control path
.IP "running" 12
qdisc running seqcount (might be NULL)
.IP "opt" 12
rate estimator configuration TLV
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Replaces the configuration of a rate estimator by calling
\fBgen_kill_estimator\fP and \fBgen_new_estimator\fP.

Returns 0 on success or a negative error code.
